Tips for using these templates
Run through templates in order. The sequence is deliberate — task clarity must come before data or model decisions.
Blanks that typically cause the most friction (and reveal the most useful gaps):
•	"N examples" — teams almost always overestimate how much labeled data they have.
•	"Does / does not contain PII" — in financial services, the answer is almost always does.
•	Success metric + threshold — if these can't be filled in, the project isn't ready to start.
